Your questions have been answered: "The RFQ grid isn't wired to the Theming API (it's on legacy ag-theme-alpine), so spec §4's withParams edits won't render. How should I proceed with Step 1's theming?"="The ::ng-deep rules in SPEC_V2 §5 are all still correct — they target real AG Grid classes and work on Alpine. The only thing that breaks is §4's withParams() block. Replace that one block with CSS variables on the Alpine wrapper. Everything else in the spec stays the same.

Replacement for SPEC_V2 §4 (Step 1 only)
Instead of editing grid-themes.config.ts, add this block to rfq.component.scss:

// rfq.component.scss — Alpine CSS variable overrides
// Replaces the themeQuartz.withParams() block from SPEC_V2 §4.
// All ::ng-deep rules in §5 stay exactly as written.

::ng-deep .ag-theme-alpine {
  // ── Accent ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  --ag-alpine-active-color:             #D81B60;
  --ag-range-selection-background-color: rgba(216, 27, 96, 0.07);
  --ag-range-selection-border-color:    #D81B60;
  --ag-checkbox-checked-color:          #D81B60;

  // ── Backgrounds ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  --ag-background-color:                #ffffff;
  --ag-odd-row-background-color:        #fbfcfd;
  --ag-row-hover-color:                 #fff5f8;
  --ag-selected-row-background-color:   #fff5f8;
  --ag-header-background-color:         #f7f9fc;

  // ── Text ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  --ag-foreground-color:                #475569;
  --ag-header-foreground-color:         #475569;
  --ag-secondary-foreground-color:      #7b8a9a;

  // ── Borders ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  --ag-border-color:                    #e7e9ee;
  --ag-secondary-border-color:          #eef1f5;
  --ag-row-border-color:                #eef1f5;
  --ag-border-radius:                   8px;

  // ── Typography ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  --ag-font-size:                       13px;
  --ag-font-family:
    "Hanken Grotesk", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif;
}
Exact replacement text for the Claude Code Step 1 prompt
Replace the "Step 1" block in your Claude Code prompt with this:

Step 1 (lowest risk): Visual reskin via Alpine CSS variables + ::ng-deep CSS.

The RFQ grid is on legacy ag-theme-alpine, NOT the Theming API. Do NOT touch
grid-themes.config.ts. Do NOT write themeQuartz.withParams(). Instead:

1a. In rfq.component.scss, add a ::ng-deep .ag-theme-alpine { } block and set
the CSS variables listed in SPEC_V2.md §4 "Replacement block." These variables
are the correct mechanism for the Alpine theme — they set background, row hover,
selection, header, accent, borders, font family, and font size.

1b. All ::ng-deep rules in SPEC_V2.md §5 (header heights, group-band tints, seam
shadow, row group rows, scenario cell tints, re-quote cell, button styles, status
bar) are correct as written. Apply them to rfq.component.scss exactly as the spec
says — the mechanism tags ([::ng-deep CSS], [colDef cellClass], etc.) are all valid
for the Alpine theme.

1c. headerFontWeight, headerFontSize, cellHorizontalPadding, and text-transform
uppercase on header text have no Alpine CSS variable equivalents — handle them
with ::ng-deep CSS rules (already specified in SPEC_V2 §5a).

This is pure CSS — zero logic or API changes. Show me the diff before committing.
Two things to tell Claude Code if it gets confused
If it tries to write --ag-header-font-weight — that's not a real Alpine variable; stop it and use ::ng-deep .ag-header-cell-text { font-weight: 600 } instead.
If it writes --ag-* variables outside .ag-theme-alpine — they won't scope correctly; the block must be ::ng-deep .ag-theme-alpine { }.". You can now continue with these answers in mind.

