---

### groupHeaderHeight

```typescript
/**
 * The height in pixels for the rows containing header column groups. If not specified, it uses `headerHeight`.
 * 
 */
number
```

---

The grid contains thousands of elements. Most of them respond to the `spacing` parameter, by having their default padding defined as a multiple of it. But many of them don't have their own specific parameters to customise size. For all elements except rows, headers and list items (see note below), you can set their height, margin or paddings using CSS rules that target a class name, e.g.


```
.ag-panel-title-bar {
    height: 80px;
}
```


### Setting the height of rows, headers and list items


To change the height of rows, headers and list item heights, you *must* use the provided parameters `rowHeight`, `headerHeight` and `listItemHeight`, or the equivalent CSS custom properties `--ag-row-height`, `--ag-header-height` and `--ag-list-item-height`. The grid uses [DOM virtualisation](ag-mcp://article/dom-virtualisation) for rendering large amounts of data, and needs to know the height of virtualised elements in order to calculate their layout. It does this by measuring the values of CSS variables such as `--ag-row-height`.


Using CSS to set a height on a row element itself e.g. `.ag-row { height: 50px; }` is not supported.


---

Column Headers can be styled using CSS classes and inline styles via `headerClass` and `headerStyle` properties. Header heights can also be configured and set to adjust automatically based on content.


See [Styling & Height](ag-mcp://article/column-headers-styling) for full documentation on:


* [Header Style](ag-mcp://article/column-headers-styling) and [Header Class](ag-mcp://article/column-headers-styling)
* [Header Height](ag-mcp://article/column-headers-styling)
* [Auto Header Height](ag-mcp://article/column-headers-styling)
* [Text Orientation](ag-mcp://article/column-headers-styling)


